summary: you saw captain marvel 11 times at the movies??
question: you saw captain marvel 11 times at the movies??
answer:
..but yeah, I went by myself a a few times because I get six free cinema tickets with my bank, and I also get 2 for 1 with my pet insurance.

So I had like a whole bunch of cinema tickets and a whole bunch of people that wanted to see it, so I just kept going.

My wallet, for the month of March, was just bulging with cinema tickets, and I still have them all, they’re on my notice board.


Side note: the only other films I saw at the cinema more than twice were Scott Pilgrim vs. The World at 6, Star Wars: The Force Awakens and Rogue One: A Star Wars Story at 4, and Kong: Skull Island at 3. 

Two of these films (three including Captain Marvel) have Brie Larson in them. She’s just that good, man. She stars in good movies, my dudes!

But it wasn’t until being in the theater seeing ‘Wonder Woman’… I was like, ‘Why is this making me cry so much?’ I realized ’cause I hadn’t had that, and there was a kid in me that was like, ‘Oh, my God.
